#. <section class="sutta" id="an7.69"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.69:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.69:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Greater Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an7.69:0.3"
msgid "69. Pāricchattakasutta"
msgstr "69. The Shady Orchid Tree"

# BB has “coral tree”, but it seems this is an old mistake. It is the Orchid Tree, http://www.flowersofindia.net/catalog/slides/Kachnar.html
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro "
"paṇḍupalāso hoti, attamanā, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā tasmiṃ samaye honti:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when the leaves on the Shady Orchid Tree belonging to the gods "
"of the Thirty-Three turn brown, the gods are elated. They think:"

msgctxt "an7.69:1.2"
msgid ""
"‘paṇḍupalāso dāni pāricchattako koviḷāro nacirasseva dāni pannapalāso "
"bhavissatī’ti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"‘Now the leaves on the Shady Orchid Tree have turned brown! It won’t be long "
"until they fall.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:2.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro "
"pannapalāso hoti, attamanā, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā tasmiṃ samaye honti:"
msgstr "When the leaves have fallen, the gods are elated. They think:"

# I follow BB’s botanical interpretation here, but use more colloquial terms. I doubt if the devas sounded like botany textbooks.
msgctxt "an7.69:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘pannapalāso dāni pāricchattako koviḷāro nacirasseva dāni jālakajāto "
"bhavissatī’ti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"‘Now the leaves on the Shady Orchid Tree have fallen. It won’t be long until "
"its foliage starts to regrow.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro "
"jālakajāto hoti, attamanā, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā tasmiṃ samaye honti:"
msgstr "When the foliage starts to regrow, the gods are elated. They think:"

msgctxt "an7.69:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘jālakajāto dāni pāricchattako koviḷāro nacirasseva dāni khārakajāto "
"bhavissatī’ti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"‘Now the foliage of the Shady Orchid Tree has started to regrow. It won’t be "
"long until it’s ready to grow flowers and leaves separately.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:4.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro "
"khārakajāto hoti, attamanā, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā tasmiṃ samaye honti:"
msgstr ""
"When it’s ready to grow flowers and leaves separately, the gods are elated. "
"They think:"

#. VAR: kuṭumalakajāto → kuḍumalakajāto (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.69:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘khārakajāto dāni pāricchattako koviḷāro nacirasseva dāni kuṭumalakajāto "
"bhavissatī’ti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"‘Now the Shady Orchid Tree is ready to grow flowers and leaves separately. "
"It won’t be long until buds start to form.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.118"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:5.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro "
"kuṭumalakajāto hoti, attamanā, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā tasmiṃ samaye honti:"
msgstr "When the buds start to form, the gods are elated. They think:"

#. VAR: korakajāto → kokāsakajāto (bj, s1-3, pts1) | kosakajāto (mr)
msgctxt "an7.69:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘kuṭumalakajāto dāni pāricchattako koviḷāro nacirasseva dāni korakajāto "
"bhavissatī’ti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"‘Now the buds of the Shady Orchid Tree have started to form. It won’t be "
"long until the buds burst.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:6.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro "
"korakajāto hoti, attamanā, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā tasmiṃ samaye honti:"
msgstr "When the buds have burst, the gods are elated. They think:"

#. VAR: sabbaphāliphullo → sabbapāliphullo (bj)
msgctxt "an7.69:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘korakajāto dāni pāricchattako koviḷāro nacirasseva dāni sabbaphāliphullo "
"bhavissatī’ti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"‘Now the buds of the Shady Orchid Tree have burst. It won’t be long until it "
"fully blossoms.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:7.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro "
"sabbaphāliphullo hoti, attamanā, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā pāricchattakassa "
"koviḷārassa mūle dibbe cattāro māse pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā "
"samaṅgībhūtā paricārenti. (7)"
msgstr ""
"When the Shady Orchid Tree of the gods of the Thirty-Three has fully "
"blossomed, the gods are elated. For four celestial months they amused "
"themselves at the root of the tree, supplied and provided with the five "
"kinds of sensual stimulation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:8.1"
msgid ""
"Sabbaphāliphullassa kho pana, bhikkhave, pāricchattakassa koviḷārassa "
"samantā paññāsayojanāni ābhāya phuṭaṃ hoti, anuvātaṃ yojanasataṃ gandho "
"gacchati, ayamānubhāvo pāricchattakassa koviḷārassa."
msgstr ""
"When the Shady Orchid Tree has fully blossomed, its radiance spreads for "
"fifty leagues, while its fragrance wafts for a hundred leagues. Such is the "
"majesty of the Shady Orchid Tree."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:9.1"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yasmiṃ samaye ariyasāvako agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajjāya ceteti, paṇḍupalāso, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako tasmiṃ samaye hoti "
"devānaṃva tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro. (1)"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a noble disciple plans to go go forth from the lay "
"life to homelessness, they’re like the Shady Orchid Tree when its leaves "
"turn brown."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:10.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni "
"acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, pannapalāso, bhikkhave, "
"ariyasāvako tasmiṃ samaye hoti devānaṃva tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako "
"koviḷāro. (2)"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple shaves off their hair and beard, dresses in ocher "
"robes, and goes forth from the lay life to homelessness, they’re like the "
"Shady Orchid Tree when its leaves fall."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:11.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ "
"jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected,"

msgctxt "an7.69:11.2"
msgid ""
"jālakajāto, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako tasmiṃ samaye hoti devānaṃva tāvatiṃsānaṃ "
"pāricchattako koviḷāro. (3)"
msgstr "they’re like the Shady Orchid Tree when its foliage starts to regrow."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:12.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … "
"dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,"
msgstr ""
"When, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a "
"noble disciple enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the "
"rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, "
"and unification of mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected,"

msgctxt "an7.69:12.2"
msgid ""
"khārakajāto, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako tasmiṃ samaye hoti devānaṃva "
"tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro. (4)"
msgstr ""
"they’re like the Shady Orchid Tree when it’s ready to grow flowers and "
"leaves separately."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.119"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:13.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati,"
msgstr ""
"When, with the fading away of rapture, a noble disciple enters and remains "
"in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and "
"aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss’,"

msgctxt "an7.69:13.2"
msgid ""
"kuṭumalakajāto, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako tasmiṃ samaye hoti devānaṃva "
"tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro. (5)"
msgstr "they’re like the Shady Orchid Tree when its buds start to form."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:14.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā "
"… pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,"
msgstr ""
"When, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, "
"a noble disciple enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness,"

msgctxt "an7.69:14.2"
msgid ""
"korakajāto, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako tasmiṃ samaye hoti devānaṃva tāvatiṃsānaṃ "
"pāricchattako koviḷāro. (6)"
msgstr "they’re like the Shady Orchid Tree when its buds burst."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:15.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharati,"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life, and they live having realized it with their own "
"insight due to the ending of defilements,"

msgctxt "an7.69:15.2"
msgid ""
"sabbaphāliphullo, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako tasmiṃ samaye hoti devānaṃva "
"tāvatiṃsānaṃ pāricchattako koviḷāro. (7)"
msgstr "they’re like the Shady Orchid tree when it fully blossoms."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.120"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an7.69:16.1"
msgid "Tasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye bhummā devā saddamanussāventi:"
msgstr "At that time the earth gods raised the cry:"

msgctxt "an7.69:16.2"
msgid ""
"‘eso itthannāmo āyasmā itthannāmassa āyasmato saddhivihāriko amukamhā gāmā "
"vā nigamā vā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This venerable named so-and-so, from such-and-such village or town, the "
"pupil of the venerable named so-and-so, went forth from the lay life to "
"homelessness. They’ve realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own "
"insight due to the ending of defilements.’"

msgctxt "an7.69:16.3"
msgid "Bhummānaṃ devānaṃ saddaṃ sutvā cātumahārājikā devā … pe …"
msgstr "Hearing the cry of the Earth Gods, the Gods of the Four Great Kings …"

msgctxt "an7.69:16.4"
msgid "tāvatiṃsā devā …"
msgstr "the Gods of the Thirty-Three …"

msgctxt "an7.69:16.5"
msgid "yāmā devā …"
msgstr "the Gods of Yama …"

msgctxt "an7.69:16.6"
msgid "tusitā devā …"
msgstr "the Joyful Gods …"

msgctxt "an7.69:16.7"
msgid "nimmānaratī devā …"
msgstr "the Gods Who Love to Create …"

msgctxt "an7.69:16.8"
msgid "paranimmitavasavattī devā …"
msgstr "the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others …"

msgctxt "an7.69:16.9"
msgid "brahmakāyikā devā saddamanussāventi:"
msgstr "the Gods of Brahmā’s Group raised the cry:"

msgctxt "an7.69:16.10"
msgid ""
"‘eso itthannāmo āyasmā itthannāmassa āyasmato saddhivihāriko amukamhā gāmā "
"vā nigamā vā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This venerable named so-and-so, from such-and-such village or town, the "
"pupil of the venerable named so-and-so, went forth from the lay life to "
"homelessness. They’ve realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own "
"insight due to the ending of defilements.’"

#. VAR: brahmalokā saddo → sādhukārasaddo (bj-a, Ma-aka aṭṭha.)
msgctxt "an7.69:16.11"
msgid ""
"Itiha tena khaṇena tena muhuttena yāva brahmalokā saddo abbhuggacchati, "
"ayamānubhāvo khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno”ti."
msgstr ""
"And so in a moment, in an instant, the sound soared up to the Brahmā realm.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.69:16.12"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
